<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7177970>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Main islands or archipelagos of the Tropical South Pacific (TSP, above).The Cook Islands, as a country, includes Pukapuka coral atoll in the northern group; the present survey is restricted to the three large islands—Rarotonga, Aitutaki and Mangaia—of the Cook Islands southern group, boxed in blue above and enlarged below. Atolls and smaller islands in the Cook Islands southern group are named in grey below (see also Fig. 2 and Tables 1–3)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7177970/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

